D 1 - Standing roots
Description:
These non-floating standing roots are great for the Amazonian-themed setups, they do not need to be soaked or glued, and can be used immediately. They provide a lot of hiding places for various types of fish and can be made in the colors of your choice.

\n

Their maximum height in the set is 70 cm (28"). Please specify the height you would like. If not specified, their height will be 70 cm (28").
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 2 - Standing logs
Description:
These non-floating standing logs are very popular with Discus fish keepers but are great for all species in general. They come in sets of 7, 10, 15 and 20, and are grouped on single larger stands. For example, a set of 10 logs can be grouped like this: 3 + 3 + 4 logs.

\n

Please specify how you would like them grouped and their height (the maximum is 70 cm (28")). If not specified, their height will be 70 cm (28"). Their diameters are around 4-10 cm
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 3 - Standing logs
Description:
These non-floating standing logs model D3 are very popular with Discus fish keepers, but are great for all species in general. The logs are hollow inside and can be installed in several ways- siliconed to the bottom of the tank; a few small stones can be placed in them to keep them in place; a few stones can be placed around them to keep them in place; a small amount of sand can be placed inside them to keep them in place, and other.

\n

Their maximum height in the set is 70 cm (28"). Please specify the height you would like. If not specified, their height will be 70 cm (28"). Their diameters are around 4-12 cm
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 4 - Logs
Description:
These non-floating logs are great if you want to add logs to your aquarium, but you don’t want to soak them and deal with issues that come with it. They don’t need to be soaked, weighed down or glued. They come in different shapes, length and colors.

\n

Their maximum length in the set is 70 cm (28"). Please specify the length of the logs you would like. If not specified, they will be made in random lengths.
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 5 – Rocks
Description:
These non-floating rocks don’t need to be soaked or siliconed, can be moved around, taken out and re-used. They are hollow, so in order for them to stay at the bottom of the tank, you will need to fill them with water and place them in the desired place in your tank.

\n

Please specify the size of your tank and we will make the rocks in the appropriate sizes. You can also specify the color of the rocks (they can be made in the colors of any background model).
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 6 – Rocks(floating)
Description:
These floating rocks need to be glued to stay at the bottom of the aquarium. They can also be used as overhanging rocks, in which case you can place them under the aquarium's support bars or lids, in which case the water will keep them in place. That way, you can create a stronger 3D effect and shadows on the sand.
They can be made in the colors of your choice.

Please specify the size of your tank and we will make the rocks in the appropriate sizes. You can also specify the color of the rocks (they can be made in the colors of any background model).
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 7 - Bamboo Standing logs
Description:
These non-floating standing bamboo logs come with small stands at their base and need to be siliconed to the bottom of the tank. We sell them in sets of 7, 10, 15 and 20. Standard height is 70 cm (28″).

\n

Their maximum height in the set is 70 cm (28"). Please specify the height you would like. If not specified, their height will be 70 cm (28"). Their diameters are around 2.5-9 cm
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 8 - Thin roots
Description:
These non-floating thin roots can be ordered on their own or in a combination with a background or standing logs.

\n

They can be attached to the background by poking small holes in the background, or in the logs.

\n

They are great for making your Amazonian themed aquarium look more natural, or to create hiding places for smaller fish.
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots

Name: D 9 - Catappa leaves
Description:
These natural looking artificial Catappa leaves are ready to use, they don’t need to be weighed down, don’t float and don’t change their color or rot. We make them with natural looking edges, just like they can be found in nature.

\n

They are between 10 cm and 17 cm long (4″- 7″). We usually make them in assorted colors and sizes, unless specified otherwise.
Categories: D Models - Logs\, Leaves\, Driftwood\, Rocks and Roots
Attribute 1 value(s): set of 10 pieces, set of 15 pieces, set of 20 pieces, set of 40 pieces

\n

Their maximum height in the set is 70 cm (28"). Please specify the height you would like. If not specified, their height will be 70 cm (28"). Their diameters are around 4-12 cm

Set 1
Short description:
This set consists of 6 non-floating bottom rocks and 20 artificial Catappa leaves. The rocks are hollow inside, don't need to be soaked or siliconed and can be moved around and reused an unlimited number of times. The leaves are made in natural looking brownish, reddish and yellowish tones, while the rocks are made in warm earthy tones.
\n
If you would like to order this set in different colors, make sure to leave us a note below.
\n
The approximate sizes of the rocks in this set are: HxWxD: 21x26x23 cm; 16x22x12 cm; 12x24x14 cm; 17x18x16 cm; 20x29x20 cm; 17x33x21 cm. Catappa leaves are around 9-16 cm long.

Name: Set 2
Short description:
This set contains 5 non-floating bottom rocks and one hollow log with tree bark. This log is perfect for species which need hiding spots and darker areas, as they can swim in and out of the log. These products don't have to be soaked or siliconed to the tank, they don't float and can be moved around as you wish. The rocks are made in light and dark grey tones, while the log is made in dark brown tones with some warmer accents. If you would like to order this set in different colors, make sure to leave us a note below.
\n
The approximate sizes of the rocks in this set are: HxWxD: 10x20x18 cm; 17x18x13 cm; 19x29x20 cm; 8x21x9 cm; 18x26x20 cm.
\n
The size of the log is 80 cm long, around 10-12 cm wide.

Name: Set 3
Short description:
This set consists of 4 non-floating bottom rocks in warm, reddish, earthy tones and one hollow log. The design of the rocks is inspired by 3D backgrounds that resemble laminated rocks. This log is perfect for species which prefer to hide in darker spots, as they can swim in and out of the log. These products don't have to be soaked or siliconed to the tank, they don't float and can be moved around as you wish. If you would like to order this set in different colors, make sure to leave us a note below. \n
The approximate sizes of the rocks in this set are: HxWxD: 8x37x23 cm; 12x22x16 cm; 8x21x13 cm; 12x38x23 cm. The size of the log is 80 cm long, around 10-12 cm wide.

Name: Set 4
Short description:
This set consists of 4 standing logs, one "fallen" log and one hollow log with tree bark. The standing logs are 70 cm tall, while the hollow log with tree bark is around 80 cm long. This setup is suggested for Amazonian themed setups or similar. Fish can hide in the hollow log, while Discus fish just love standing logs.
\n
All logs in the set can be shorter than 70 cm if you would like, so please make sure to leave us a note below.
\n
The standing logs can be siliconed to the bottom of the tank, or on small glass/ceramic plates and then placed in the tank like that. The logs don't need to be soaked before use and can be reused an unlimited number of times

Name: Set 5

The height of the roots is 70 cm, but they can be made shorter per your request. The approximate sizes of the rocks are: H:W:D: 18x22x10 cm; 18x22x12 cm; 16x36x22 cm; 22x24x19 cm; 16x36x22 cm. If you would like to order this set in different colors, make sure to leave us a note below.

Description:
These non-floating, free standing roots are perfect for all types of Amazonian setups. They don't need to be weighed down, soaked or glued. Order them in a set or with your favorite background. Roots come in various sizes, and you can specify the height of each root in the field below. If you don't specify their height, we will make them in random sizes. If you want roots taller than 70 cm (28"), please email us.

The maximum height of the roots is 70 cm (28″). They are around 20-30 cm (10″-13″) wide at the base.

D 48 – Rocks
Description:
Create a complete atmosphere for your Malawi and Tanganyika cichlids with the original shape of the stone of Lake Malawi and Tanganyika. Rocks can be made with or without holes.

\n

The advantage of the holes is that the spawning is significantly increased in the sense of the natural habitat of Lake Malawi and Lake Tanganyika, and the holes help to hide or guard the young during spawning and at the same time enable unhindered spawning inside the rocks.

\n

The holes can be placed to be seen by the observer's eye as well as not to be seen, i.e. to face the rear glass. The choice is yours. All rocks can be made in any color or in the color of the background you order.
